paragraphs.text:
%md  Trafi data workshop 22.01.2015
========================
*** 
### Data description ###
[Trafi ](http://www.trafi.fi/en/services/open_data) has published open data for vehichle data since 2014. Data is extracted from the **Vehicular and Driver Data Register** and it  includes over
5 million rows with 38 columns. The size of the data is about 829MB and it is CSV formatted. It is similar to a classic R [mtcars](https://stat.ethz.ch/R-manual/R-devel/library/datasets/html/mtcars.html) dataset.
### Apache Zeppelin
* first release  under Apache incubator 1st August 2015
* it has many  built-in interpreters:spark,pyspark,sql,md,sh
* there are at least three different way to visualise data

### Apache Spark
* the most active project inside Hadoop ecosystem
* open source big data processing framework built around speed, ease of use
* designed for data science
* programs are much shorter  than traditional MapReduce equivalents
* scala,java,R,python implementations

### d3.js
* data driven documents
* javascript library for producing dynamic, interactive data visualizations in web browsers

paragraphs.text: %md We have made our first visualisation. Let's continue with

%sql select firstRegistrationDate,count(firstRegistrationDate) as count from mtcars_p where year(firstRegistrationDate) > 2005  
     group by firstRegistrationDate
     order by firstRegistrationDate

%sql select firstRegistrationDate,count(firstRegistrationDate) as count from mtcars_p where year(firstRegistrationDate) between "${start year}" and
 "${end year}"
     group by firstRegistrationDate
     order by firstRegistrationDate
%md Note,that the high values are usually at end of the month. Also on weekend there only a few events
% Lets select the ten most popular brands.

%sql select brandAsPlaintext as brand,count(brandAsPlaintext) as brandcount from mtcars
     where  vehicleCategory = "M1" and year(firstRegistrationDate) > 1975 
     group by  brandAsPlaintext
     order by  brandcount desc limit 10
